n\nfactors is very important by calculation of continuum spectra corrections. As\nthe examples we present the estimates for a few stars from Pulkovo\nspectrophotometric catalog and for the Sun. The influence of temperature\nfluctuations on color indices of observed cosmic objects is also investigated.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 Apr 2012 08:55:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 31 May 2012 12:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 23 Jul 2012 09:23:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-04"}
