llations in the\ntail of X-ray bursts is associated with a systematic behaviour of the spectral\nparameters in that phase of the bursts. This result is consistent with\npredictions of models that associate the oscillations in the tail of X-ray\nbursts with the propagation of a cooling wake in the material on the\nneutron-star surface during the decay of the bursts.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 Apr 2012 13:58:18 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 12 Sep 2013 14:17:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-04"}
